diff:1670194083:1670123692:=52,66c52%0a%3c #foxbegin 221204-224803-84000#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!ASL Interpreters at Disney Parks %0a%3c -> - ellenangwin1%0a%3c -> [-04.12.2022 - 14:48-]%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 221204-224803-84000 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c Since 1973, Disney Parks have included ASL interpreters at some (but not all) activities across the park, including live performances. In a video that recently went viral on TikTok, a park visitor shared the performance of two ASL interpreters who were working at a live show of Beauty and the Beast. The video was captioned “Disney give these interpreters a RAISE!” Several videos like this have been posted to TikTok and have received hundreds of thousands of likes. The interpreters not only sign the words that are spoken on stage, they also act out the scenes along with the actors. This passionate and energetic interpretation allows the Deaf community to enjoy the performance along with the hearing community.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 221204-224803-84000#%0a---%0a> %0a
